article.headline: Montana 45, N. Arizona 10
article.story: MISSOULA, Mont. -- Chase Reynolds rushed for 157 yards and three touchdowns and Cole Bergquist passed for 186 yards and three more scores in Montana's 45-10 win over Northern Arizona Saturday. Montana (8-1, 4-1) took advantage of early turnovers to take a 28-0 lead on a 9-yard scoring pass from Bergquist to Mike Ferriter just three minutes into the second quarter. The teams traded field goals before Reynolds scored on a 67-yard run with 9:07 left in the third to give the Grizzlies a 38-3 lead. Ferriter had four catches for 56 yards and two touchdowns while Marc Mariani had three catches for 60 yards and a score. The Grizzlies, ranked sixth in the Sports Network Poll, rushed for 223 yards against No. 19 NAU (6-3, 4-2) which had been allowing its opponents less than 19 yards rushing per game. Deonte Williams rushed for 105 yards and a touchdown for the Lumberjacks.
